<br>
But if you're going to drag me into this, be accurate. Magister never did any sort of &quot;hard sell&quot; to get me to join, nor were they the reason I left Affliction in the first place. Despite what some people say about Magister, they are not the Siren Song of Erollisi Marr - had I not felt they were the guild for me, I wouldn't have joined them (a good 5-6 months AFTER I left Affliction, by the way). They didn't hypnotize or brainwash me. Ana didn't send me a tape that had subliminals on it saying: Join Magister for Phat Lewt...<br>
<br>
Use the argument that my best friend (Anastia) was in Magister and so she must have tried to recruit me. WRONG. Ana, as any good friend would, wanted me to enjoy playing. She left Affliction LONG before I did. Had I really only joined the guild for her, I would have left when she did.<br>
<br>
I'll end by saying that bringing her name, and mine, into a thread about &quot;using guilds&quot; is tasteless, and I would have thought below the people who brought us up. This implies that both Anastia and myself &quot;used&quot; Affliction to our own ends and bailed. Neither Anastia nor myself got our epic while in Affliction. I can't think of anything truly &quot;uber&quot; that we scored and then took with us when we left (I returned the Elder Spiritist Arms and the Golem Tear Ring loaned to me by Gloriana, as well as one of those Chardok shields that sell for nothing now to... Nocrad maybe - an officer.). I did retain one thing, a Crystal Chitin Chestplate that up until about 2 months ago, I was still using. If you guys wanna talk to me about getting some sort of reimbursement for that, just let me know and I'll be happy to pay you what you think it was worth to you.<br>
<br>
